<TEXT>
a firstterm state representative and 
physician is in the center of floridas abortion storm this week 
because hes the only legislator who performs abortions making him 
a lightning rod for protests 
ben graber even gets hate mail 
they need something to marshal their forces around he said 
of abortion opponents the obstetriciangynecologists pompano 
beach womens clinic drew a raucous demonstration saturday three 
days before the state legislature was to begin a special session on 
abortion called by gov bob martinez 
they were frustrated by the florida supreme court decision 
they decided to make me the target an ideal situation with the 
legislative session coming up graber said monday 
the state supreme court last week cited the state privacy law to 
strike down a 1988 statute requiring minors to get parental consent 
for abortion uphold a womans unrestricted right to abortion in 
the first trimester and emphasize individual privacy rights in 
abortion decisionmaking 
the governor acted within weeks of the us supreme courts july 
3 ruling upholding missouri state restrictions on abortions making 
florida the first state since then to call a session devoted to 
abortion 
at saturdays demonstration graber said several of his 
patients none there for abortions were jostled by a 200strong 
crowd and others were scared away graber says he performs two or 
three abortions a week and only as part of his practice 
the rev pat mahoney a south florida coordinator for operation 
rescue an antiabortion group that demonstrates at clinics was 
arrested and charged with assault on a police officer obstructing 
justice without violence and trepassing 
graber called operation rescue a terrorist organization and 
said he will seek a restraining order against the group and damages 
his office has been picketed before but the latest protest was 
perhaps the most strident he said 
graber among many legislators who opposes holding the special 
session said his mail has gone in recent weeks from evenly split 
to mostly antiabortion 
there have been more gory pictures of fetuses and more hate 
mail said graber a germanborn jew offended by packets with 
pictures of hitler and fetuses that contend aborting fetuses is 
comparable to the holocaust 
someone wrote its too bad hitler didnt finish off your 
family he said 
thousands of activists on both sides of the abortion issue are 
flocking here this week but graber is confident legislators will be 
protected by capitol and local police who have set up command 
posts and video monitors and trained a 40member riot squad 
being in the middle of demonstrations isnt the role graber 
wants to play 
id like to be there to cut through the propaganda be 
available to ask questions and answer questions and make sure the 
facts come out in an intelligent manner graber said 
last month he circulated a legislators guide to abortion 
issues graber said his 27page handbook has been positively 
received although antiabortion forces say he shouldnt 
necessarily be considered an expert 
said state rep tom banjanin i think every member of the 
legislature is very knowledgeable on this issue i think abortions 
are the murder of unborn children 
i question whether he can approach this issue objectively 
considering that he has a profit motive involved in what can come 
out of this session added jon johnson political director for 
florida right to life 
graber 41 in practice for 12 years said he initially opposed 
abortions which were illegal when he entered medical school at 
texas tech university 
he said abortions are only a small part of his practice and that 
many are performed on older women whose health could be jeopardized 
by pregnancy 
graber married father of daughters ages 18 17 and 12 years 
has proposed a statewide study panel 
everythings not blackandwhite on this issue he said 
now were talking about a threeday session where were going to 
solve all these complicated questions its unrealistic 
</TEXT>
