<TEXT>
chinas communist government is holding a big 
bash this year for the 2540th birthday of confucius the 
philosopher once reviled for his reactionary ideas 
the old sage while still taken to task as a father of chinese 
feudalism has now entered the party pantheon as a thinker who 
embodied such socialist virtues as harmony stability and obedience 
new communist party general secretary jiang zemin in a meeting 
with confucian scholars sunday described confucius 551479 bc 
as a great ancient thinker of china 
the official xinhua news agency quoted jiang as adding it is 
necessary to select the essence while discarding the dross from his 
thought the good side of his thought in particular should be 
used to educate the younger generation in helping them inherit and 
carry forward fine national traditions 
some 300 scholars from 20 nations are holding a symposium on 
confucian thought in beijing and confucius birthplace of qufu 300 
miles to the south it is being cosponsored by the un education 
science and culture organization 
an exhibition on confucius life and work also opened at the 
capital museum a former confucian temple sacrificial rites were 
observed the first time beijing has staged a largescale ceremony 
in memory of confucius since the communist takeover in 1949 
qufu is also holding its first confucius cultural festival to 
mark the sept 28 birth of the sage whose ideas on filial piety and 
social order still wield considerable influence in such asian 
countries as south korea singapore and japan 
much of the hoopla has been part of chinas efforts to revive 
its flagging tourist industry and develop qufu as a tourist town 
but it also reflects the new appraisal of the old thinker 
the confucian tenets of loyalty stability sacrificing oneself 
for the social good and obedience to ones masters have won favor 
from the current communist government which is now seeking to 
reassert control after crushing the prodemocracy movement this 
spring 
confucianism which through chinese history gained religious 
status with its own temples was often been a target of chinese 
progressives 
leaders of the may 4th movement of 1919 chinas first 
studentled campaign for democratic reform said it represented 
agrarian feudal values denigrated women and showed excessive 
respect for precedence creating an obstacle to progress 
mao tsetungs revolutionaries with their determination to 
overturn traditional class order rejected confucius while seizing 
the same mandate of heaven the scholar once bestowed on the 
imperial family 
in 1973 the cultural revolution government launched a massive 
anticonfucius antilin biao campaign linking lin maos 
heirapparent who died in a plane crash after failing to 
assassinate mao in 1971 to confucius reactionary ideology 
the movement assailed those trying to restore feudalism 
capitalism and revisionism and accused confucius of advocating 
the establishment of a slave society 
after the 196676 cultural revolution ended confucius was 
rehabilitated 
for centuries people have either exalted and glorified him 
or disparaged and belittled him the official china daily said 
monday in an article on the profound influence of confucian 
ideas on contemporary china 
but none can add to or detract from his position in chinese 
history as an outstanding thinker statesman educator and 
classicist deserving to be called a cultural giant of the world 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

