study said today 
the soviets no longer need so many tanks because their latest 
models are superior in some cases to those of the west in armor 
mobility and firepower said christopher f foss editor of the 
19891990 edition of the respected janes armor and artillery 
foss wrote in his foreword to the volume describing the worlds 
armored vehicles and towed guns that the past year was dominated by 
the soviet decision to withdraw some of its conventional forces 
