<TEXT>
an air force jet plunged to earth and 
exploded during an air show after the pilot apparently misjudged 
his altitude and tried an extra maneuver the flier was killed and 
dozens of spectators were injured fleeing the fiery wreckage 
the crash sunday was the 15th this year for the indian air 
force which has the worlds highest accident rate defense 
statistics show 
the mirage 2000 fighter jet crashed at indian air force day 
celebrations the pilot ramesh bakshi the 39yearold commander 
of the mirage squadron was killed instantly 
dozens of panicked spectators suffered sprained ankles bruises 
or broken bones while running toward or away from the giant 
fireball 
