that drug addiction has become a problem in the region 
liu wen director of criminal investigation in the ministry of 
public security said he did not know the number of addicts and 
all poppy crops found have been eradicated 
both problems were byproducts of a growing transit trade in 
drugs from southeast asia through southern china to hong kong and 
macao he said 
liu spoke at a news conference at the end of a fiveday 
conference on drug law enforcement in asia organized by interpol 
the meeting closed to reporters was an important conference of 
practical significance liu said 
he said the 79 delegates from 32 countries and regions adopted a 
10point resolution calling on their governments to make antidrug 
efforts a top priority and strengthen international cooperation 
including financial assistance for underdeveloped countries 
fighting drug trafficking 
they also called on interpol to study the possiblity of setting 
up a drug law enforcement training center in asia 
interpol officials said chinas drug problem remains relatively 
small but yuan yongyuan deputy director of criminal 
investigation said the number of drug trafficking cases discovered 
in 1988 reached 268 up from just 56 the year before he said 
police seized 525 pounds of opium in 1988 nearly double the 1987 
amount and 365 pounds of heroin nearly four times the 1987 amount 
partial figures for 1989 showed continued increase he said 
after eliminating drugs for 30 years many people in china 
are not prepared and are not paying enough attention including 
police and customs officials he said they cannot recognize 
heroin and opium 
opium addiction was one of chinas most serious social problems 
in the early part of the century after taking power in 1949 the 
communists executed drug traffickers and reeducated users for 
decades the government said drug abuse had been wiped out 
yuan blamed its reemergence on chinas increased foreign 
contacts since 1978 and especially the relaxed policy on allowing 
hong kong residents to enter the mainland 
hong kong residents have been convicted in several drug 
smuggling cases in recent years one was executed in february after 
being convicted of recruiting three mainland chinese in a smuggling 
scheme opium and heroin are brought into southern chinas yunnan 
province from burma thailand and laos and on to canton and hong 
kong for sale to the west 
