<TEXT>
the united states will continue producing new 
chemical weapons over a 10year period even if it signs an 
international treaty to abolish all poison gas stockpiles an 
administration official said monday 
the text of the treaty being negotiated by about 40 nations in 
geneva proposes that all production be stopped immediately and that 
the plants be rendered inoperable 
however the administration will seek modifications to ensure 
that it can keep its stockpiles up to date even as it scales them 
down said the official who declined to be identified 
president bush in a sept 25 speech to the united nations said 
that once a global treaty is signed the united states will destroy 
98 percent of its chemical weapons over an eightyear period if 
the soviet union takes idetical action 
bush said the remaining stockpiles would be destroyed over the 
next two years if all nations capable of building chemical 
weapons sign that total ban treaty 
the us stockpile consists of unitary weapons many of 
which are leaking and deemed unsafe and newer binary weapons 
that use two components to make them lethal 
congress has instructed the administration to destroy the 
unitary weapons as the newer binary weapons are produced 
you dont want to get eight years down the road and have only 
unitary leaking old weapons left the official said as long 
as youre going to have any you ought to try to make sure the ones 
you have are as safe as possible 
the official said the us intention of continuing to produce 
the weapons during the phaseout period was made known to soviet 
foreign minister eduard shevardnadze during talks last month in 
wyoming with secretary of state james a baker iii 
