as the father of the pioneering economic reforms that gave 
hungarians the highest living standards in eastern europe in the 
late 1960s and early 1970s 
but in 1974 nyers was dropped from the politburo and stripped 
of his economics post as kadar put a brake on reforms that 
apparently alarmed leonid i brezhnev who then was in power in 
moscow 
nyers vast experience was the reason for his appointment last 
november as special economics minister to steer hungary through a 
period of austerity 
now he will have to steer the new party through a period of 
political transition and help it compete in the first multiparty 
elections next year 
