<TEXT>
they come from different backgrounds a 
generation apart but gregory peck and jimmy smits have one thing 
in common they both suffer stage fright 
peck gets stage fright after 45 years in films 
i always do confesses the 73yearold star who portrays the 
iconoclastic author ambrose bierce in old gringo costarring 
with jane fonda and smits 
when i went down to rehearse in mexico i was playing catchup 
because originally burt lancaster was to play the role they were 
already rehearsing and jane knew all of her lines backwards 
forwards and sideways while i was carrying a script in my hand 
when we first rehearsed a scene she embraced me her tears were 
flowing and i was trying to hold onto my script peck said 
jane was totally into the scene and i was about 8000 miles 
behind i had a bit of stage fright the first day or two that 
happens with every movie nothing unusual about that 
smits 33 had more reason to be nervous he was making the leap 
from tvs la law to a 24 million epic with two screen 
legends 
i would be lying to you if i said i wasnt nervous the first 
couple of days of shooting he said 
besides the fact that i was working with jane fonda and 
gregory peck on the first couple of days i was involved in an 
exterior scene that had 150 extras i was on a horse carrying a 
rifle and i spoke in two different languages it was an exercise in 
shifting lots of gears at the same time 
i went home that first night and i cried a little bit because 
i didnt think i was up to spec but they liked what i did 
peck speaks well of his young costar jimmy is welltrained 
and schooled holds a masters degree from cornell university in 
fine arts has worked with joe papp has done shakespeare in the 
park has done the classics hes studied voice hes studied 
movement hes a trained young artist hes ready for bigger 
things hes wonderful in la law but hes going to be a movie 
star 
peck grew up in idyllic la jolla calif the lonely son of a 
divorced druggist he became interested in acting while studying 
premed at the university of california berkeley he later went 
east to study at the neighborhood playhouse after a few stage 
roles he was signed to contracts with fox mgm selznick and rko 
and became an instant star a host of memorable roles followed 
to kill a mocking bird winning him the academy award in 1962 
pecks film roles have been sparse in recent years but he 
welcomed the challenge of playing the enigmatic bierce who wrote 
the devils dictionary 
he was pretty much a misanthrope the actor said i think 
that he had great love for his family and treated them badly and 
knew that he had i think he had great remorse about the shambles 
of his personal life also he was disappointed and disillusioned 
by the failure of his 12volume collected works 
it was in that rather gloomy mood that he decided first to go 
on a nostalgic tour of the civil war battlefields in tennessee 
where he fought as a young man he was born in 1840 then on to el 
paso and he decided well its not to late for excitement he 
decided to join the pancho villa revolution he got as far as 
chihuahua bought a white horse and set off across the desert in 
search of a band of revolutionaries he disappeared from the face 
of the earth 
old gringo is based on the carlos fuentes novel that 
fictionizes bierces fate the director is argentine luis puenzo 
whose the official story won an oscar 
peck has no plans to heat up his film career 
im working as much as i like he commented i dont want 
to do if i can avoid it anything mediocre its kind of unseemly 
at my age to come out in a turkey so im just going to sit back 
my wife and i are globetrotters we get around a lot ive had 
fun the last couple of weeks at the house ive had a stonemason a 
painter a plumber whos got to come back also a tree surgeon 
i like that kind of thing nestbuilding 
ive got four kids who are all doing interesting things he 
said one son is a banker and a freefall parachute jumper 
another is making a documentary right now in afghanistan and 
vietnam my daughter is appearing with the martha graham dance 
company in new york and my son anthony has just sold a screenplay 
to fox i follow all of them with great interest and its probably 
the most fun i have 
smits came from a different background he was born in 
manhattan son of a puerto rican mother and a father from suriname 
he was one of three children of a family of lowermiddleclass 
laborers 
we moved around a lot when i was young he recalled that 
had something to do with my becoming an actor i didnt have a lot 
of lasting friendships i played a lot by myself i madebelieve a 
lot i think that was where the acting germ was planted along 
the way there were people who influenced me to continue my 
education if i was interested in theater 
the fascinating thing is that in acting on any given day you 
can be a king or a beggar i found that i could channel my energy 
into research i was never a very good student but when it related 
to a role i could spend hours in the library researching 18th 
century england or mexico 
besides new york plays smits appeared in the films running 
scared and the believers then was cast as the dedicated 
lawyer victor sifuentes in la law that he admitted 
accelerated his career 
