<TEXT>
soichiro honda the founder of the 
japanese automaker that bears his name dropped by the henry ford 
museum on monday and recalled the day he first saw an automobile 
a model t he chased down a japanese road when he was 6 
every time that ford car stopped it left a little bit of an 
oil slick underneath and i smelled that oil slick i enjoyed it 
thoroughly and i still remember very vividly the kind of enjoyment 
i had by smelling that oil slick the 82yearold honda said 
in addition to the museum visit where he received a plaque 
honda was in the detroit area to be inducted tuesday into the 
automotive hall of fame 
he talked to reporters in front of a 1983 honda accord with a 
serial number 001 the first car to be made at the companys 
marysville ohio assembly plant 
his company was followed by other japanese automakers in 
establishing assembly plants in the united states toyota motor 
corp mazda motor corp and nissan motor corp each have wholly 
owned plants on us soil 
mitsubishi motors corp is linked with chrysler corp in a joint 
venture and fuji heavy industries inc and isuzu motors ltd own a 
plant to make subaru cars and isuzu trucks 
later this year honda begins production at its second us 
plant in east liberty ohio honda will make civic and accord cars 
at the two plants 
but honda has steered clear of linking itself with a us 
automaker it has a production agreement with the british automaker 
austin rover maker of sterling cars for the us market 
the companys founder declined to speculate on whether the 
company would join forces with any other company in the united 
states that never happened during my generation and i cannot 
answer what is going to happen in the future he said 
honda began his auto career in a tokyo repair shop at the age of 
16 in the 1930s he became involved in racing and in 1937 he 
formed a small piston ring company 
he formed honda motor co in 1948 and began producing bicycles 
the company entered the auto industry in 1963 and became a us 
manufacturer just less than 20 years later 
honda has no formal role with the company he founded i 
retired from honda motor company 16 years ago im currently 
unemployed 
yet his passion for cars and the way they work continues 
what i would really like to do even today is mess up my hands 
and work in grease he said 
</TEXT>
