ryder system inc will record a 57 million 
aftertax charge in the third quarter resulting in a loss for the 
quarter the transportation and aircraft services company said 
monday 
the charge includes an adjustment for higherthanexpected 
workers compensation loss reserves staff and facility reduction 
costs and a loss caused by the the bankruptcy filing of braniff 
airlines which had an aircraft maintenance contract with ryder 
the company said 
also included in the charge are a writedown of the carrying 
value of unprofitable small businesses in ryders vehicle leasing amp 
services division anticipated losses from the disposal of surplus 
vehicles in that division and a slowmoving parts inventory in 
ryders aviation services operation 
we are still dealing with the problems of margin and cost 
pressures in the vehicle leasing amp services division and lower auto 
production affecting the automotive carrier division said 
ryders chairman president and chief executive officer m anthony 
burns 
ryder is expected to report the quarterly loss and revenue 
figures shortly 
for 1988s third quarter ryder earned 552 million on revenue 
of 126 billion revenue for the 12 months ended june 30 totaled 
51 billion 
the company also announced monday the sale of most of its 
insurance management services division to skandia international 
insurance corp of stockholm sweden 
the sale price was not disclosed the deal is expected to close 
by years end burns said 
